      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "4d27372e12d51c98",
        "text": "The uncertainty that can accompany the increase of knowledge and the possibilities of intervention in \"natural\" processes, i.e. with their increasing availability, can be seen in an equally drastic way in almost all questions related to the development and education of the child once born."
      },
      "date": 1670009508492
